WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
I'm Philippians, the book of Philippians chapter number 4.

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:09.000
And in just a very few moments I'm going to begin reading in verse number 15 of the chapter

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:12.000
and be reading through verse number 19.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
I do want to encourage you, if you would please, to leave your Bibles handy.

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:21.000
We're going to be using them throughout the course of the Bible message this evening.

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:23.000
So good to see you. Thank you for coming.

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:28.000
I appreciate you going the extra mile to be here tonight.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:31.000
As you know, I was telling the pastor earlier in the week

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:36.000
when I was pastoring the first church that I was blessed to pastor,

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:41.000
I would be so busy looking around trying to see who wasn't there

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:46.000
that I'd often take for granted those that went the extra mile to be there.

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:51.000
And so some of you worked really hard today and some of you had a day off

00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:54.000
and you worked even harder on your day off than you have at work.

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:57.000
You're going to have to go back to work to get a break.

00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:01.000
But you made church a priority tonight and that encourages your preacher,

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:03.000
your preacher's wife, their family,

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:07.000
and that is encouraging to your fellow brothers and sisters in Christ.

00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:10.000
So thank you so much for being here tonight.

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:14.000
Let me say before we read the text out of the book of Philippians,

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:16.000
chapter number 4 this evening,

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:19.000
Cassie and I want to thank you not only for your prayerful

00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:23.000
but for your financial support every single month.

00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:27.000
You have certainly sent once again unto our necessity

00:01:27.000 --> 00:01:29.000
and I want you to know how grateful we are.

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:33.000
We could not do what God has put in our hearts to do

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:37.000
without pastors like your precious pastor

00:01:37.000 --> 00:01:40.000
and without churches like the Fellowship Baptist Church.

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:43.000
And Cassie and I are so grateful.

00:01:43.000 --> 00:01:48.000
Thank you for allowing us to be a part of your missions outreach here.

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
And thank you so much for helping us even recently

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:55.000
with our trip coming up to Brazil.

00:01:55.000 --> 00:01:59.000
A lot of folks may not realize that all of the trips that I make like that abroad

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:02.000
are at our own expense.

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:06.000
And so again, we could not do that without the help of our supporting churches.

00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:08.000
And so we're very, very appreciative.

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:10.000
We're very, very grateful.

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:14.000
Thank you for such a wonderful place to stay this week

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:17.000
at the prophet's chamber over here.

00:02:17.000 --> 00:02:19.000
I call it the land down under.

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:22.000
We're having a wonderful time in the land down under.

00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:26.000
And we're just enjoying the friendship and the fellowship of our friends

00:02:26.000 --> 00:02:29.000
right here at the Fellowship Baptist Church.

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:31.000
Now on the way out, if you would please,

00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:34.000
if you'd be so kind to come by the table,

00:02:34.000 --> 00:02:38.000
we have Macedonia's latest Focus on the Field magazines.

00:02:38.000 --> 00:02:41.000
These magazines are absolutely free of charge.

00:02:41.000 --> 00:02:45.000
And if you'd pick one up on the way out tonight, I'd appreciate it.

00:02:45.000 --> 00:02:48.000
I tell folks everywhere I go, Brother Ryan,

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
these magazines are million sellers.

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:54.000
We've got a million in the cellar.

00:02:54.000 --> 00:02:57.000
And if you could help us get them out of there and to your house,

00:02:57.000 --> 00:02:59.000
we would appreciate that.

00:02:59.000 --> 00:03:01.000
And so I've got this one.

00:03:01.000 --> 00:03:04.000
I think I've got a little bit left of another one back there as well,

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:06.000
another edition.

00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:08.000
Again, they're absolutely free of charge.

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:11.000
And if you'd pick up a prayer card and remember to pray for us,

00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:14.000
we certainly would appreciate that.

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:17.000
And then I don't normally say anything about the music,

00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:20.000
but I've just learned that if I don't say anything about it,

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:23.000
people don't even know we have music available.

00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:28.000
Every song that I've been blessed to sing this week has been recorded,

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.000
and we have CDs back there, but we also have jump drives.

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:35.000
You know, we're discovering that all of the cars these days,

00:03:35.000 --> 00:03:38.000
they don't even have CD players anymore.

00:03:38.000 --> 00:03:42.000
Now some of us in the building, we can remember cassette tapes.

00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:44.000
Can you remember that?

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:46.000
Some of you young folks have to Google that.

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:50.000
But some of you older folks, some of us can remember eight tracks, amen.

00:03:50.000 --> 00:03:52.000
And I'll just stop right there.

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:56.000
But I have jump drives of all of the music as well.

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:00.000
I see some wives nudging their husbands right there, I'm telling you.

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:03.000
And so all the jump drives are available.

00:04:03.000 --> 00:04:06.000
And a while back, some of those real techie guys in the office,

00:04:06.000 --> 00:04:12.000
they took all of my recordings over the course of the last 15 years,

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:15.000
and they put them on one jump drive.

00:04:15.000 --> 00:04:19.000
And this one jump drive right here on just that little jump drive

00:04:19.000 --> 00:04:22.000
has 15 years' worth of recordings.

00:04:22.000 --> 00:04:25.000
That's about 12 full-length CDs.

00:04:25.000 --> 00:04:27.000
That's over 120 songs recorded.

00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:30.000
And Cassie will be glad to talk to you about that.

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:34.000
That's 12 CDs for about the price of seven.

00:04:34.000 --> 00:04:38.000
And that pretty much just covers our cost for doing it.

00:04:38.000 --> 00:04:41.000
And the Lord has been so good since we've been in missions

00:04:41.000 --> 00:04:44.000
and on the road every week for the last 12 years.

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:49.000
God has worked through our CD sales to put all of the gas in our vehicles.

00:04:49.000 --> 00:04:53.000
And these days, that's a special blessing.

00:04:53.000 --> 00:04:55.000
And we're so very grateful.

00:04:55.000 --> 00:04:58.000
Well, have you found your place in the book of Philippians?

00:04:58.000 --> 00:05:01.000
If so, and if you're able, would you please stand

00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:04.000
as we read the Word of God together.

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:09.000
Your pastor and pastor's wife were so kind to take us to brunch today.

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:13.000
We had wonderful food, and the fellowship was even better.

00:05:13.000 --> 00:05:17.000
And I'm so thankful for your precious pastor and his family

00:05:17.000 --> 00:05:19.000
and their friendship to our family.

00:05:19.000 --> 00:05:22.000
And boy, didn't you enjoy the good preaching last night.

00:05:22.000 --> 00:05:25.000
Brother Ryan, boy, what a great message.

00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:28.000
I'm so impressed with Brother Ryan.

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:32.000
I text Brother Alton Beal last night after the service,

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:37.000
and I said, look, give that young man a raise. Amen.

00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:40.000
Of course, I have yet to hear anything back.

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:46.000
No, he did text me back and say, hopefully, I'll get to see you later this week.

00:05:46.000 --> 00:05:50.000
So we're hoping Brother Beal will make it before the conference is through.

00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:54.000
Philippians chapter 4 and verse 15, we'll read the text

00:05:54.000 --> 00:05:58.000
and then consider the context of the Apostle Paul's writing

00:05:58.000 --> 00:06:01.000
throughout the introduction of the message tonight.

00:06:01.000 --> 00:06:06.000
Paul writes in verse 15 of Philippians chapter 4,

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:10.000
Now ye Philippians know also that in the beginning of the gospel,

00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:13.000
when I departed from Macedonia,

00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:18.000
no church communicated with me as concerning giving and receiving,

00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:22.000
but ye only.

00:06:22.000 --> 00:06:28.000
For even in Thessalonica ye sent once again unto my necessity,

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:33.000
not because I desire a gift,

00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:38.000
but I desire fruit that may abound to your account.

00:06:38.000 --> 00:06:40.000
But I have all, and abound.

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:44.000
I am full, having received of Epaphroditus

00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:47.000
the things which were sent from you,

00:06:47.000 --> 00:06:52.000
an odor of a sweet smell, a sacrifice,

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:57.000
acceptable, well-pleasing to God.

00:06:57.000 --> 00:07:02.000
But my God shall supply all your need

00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:09.000
according to His riches in glory by Christ Jesus.

00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:12.000
Again, I want to encourage you, if you would please,

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:14.000
to leave your Bibles handy.

00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:19.000
We're going to be using them throughout the course of the message tonight.

00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:22.000
And I don't often say this, but let me just say this tonight.

00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:24.000
There's a reason why I say that.

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:26.000
Leave your Bibles handy.

00:07:26.000 --> 00:07:28.000
And here's why I say that.

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:32.000
When it comes to missions, when it comes to world evangelism,

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:35.000
when it comes to reaching the world with the gospel,

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:38.000
I have an opinion.

00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:42.000
But God did not call me to preach my opinion.

00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:47.000
I'm not here to tell you what I have to say about world evangelism.

00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:53.000
I want to take that Bible and show you what God has to say.

00:07:53.000 --> 00:07:57.000
That's why I say, leave your Bibles handy.

00:07:57.000 --> 00:08:01.000
We're going to be using them tonight throughout the course of the message

00:08:01.000 --> 00:08:09.000
as I preach on the fall the opportunity that wasn't missed in missions.

00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:10.000
Let's pray.

00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:15.000
Father, thank you for your inspired, inerrant, infallible, impeccable word.

00:08:15.000 --> 00:08:20.000
And, Lord, what a joy it is to know it's indestructible as well.

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:25.000
And, Father, we would all be very, very wise from the pulpit

00:08:25.000 --> 00:08:31.000
to the last chair in the building to not only be hearers but doers of thy word.

00:08:31.000 --> 00:08:33.000
Now, Father, I'm nothing without thee,

00:08:33.000 --> 00:08:37.000
and I long to be a blessing to these, your precious people.

00:08:37.000 --> 00:08:40.000
So I pray, therefore, you would cleanse me of sin and self

00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:44.000
and fill me with your precious Holy Spirit.

00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:47.000
If you could make a preacher out of me tonight, or if you would,

00:08:47.000 --> 00:08:49.000
I sure would appreciate it.

00:08:49.000 --> 00:08:52.000
I need you tonight, and I thank you for helping me.

00:08:52.000 --> 00:08:55.000
In Jesus' name I pray, amen.

00:08:55.000 --> 00:08:57.000
Thank you so much for standing.

00:08:57.000 --> 00:08:59.000
Please be seated.

00:08:59.000 --> 00:09:02.000
As you study Paul's epistle to the church of Philippi,

00:09:02.000 --> 00:09:06.000
one thing will become abundantly evident.

00:09:06.000 --> 00:09:10.000
Paul had a special place in his heart

00:09:10.000 --> 00:09:15.000
for his friends in the Macedonian colony of Philippi.

00:09:15.000 --> 00:09:21.000
And his friends at Philippi had a very special place in their heart

00:09:21.000 --> 00:09:24.000
for the apostle Paul.

00:09:24.000 --> 00:09:28.000
Paul loved the church of Philippi.

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:33.000
Of course, this wasn't the largest church that Paul was acquainted with.

00:09:33.000 --> 00:09:37.000
It certainly wasn't the wealthiest church.

00:09:37.000 --> 00:09:41.000
However, it would eventually become one of the most strategic churches

00:09:41.000 --> 00:09:43.000
in the New Testament record

00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:45.000
because this, ladies and gentlemen,

00:09:45.000 --> 00:09:52.000
was the church that refused to miss its opportunity in missions.

00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:56.000
Please allow me to call your attention if I may to verse 15 again.

00:09:56.000 --> 00:09:58.000
Here in verse 15,

00:09:58.000 --> 00:10:01.000
Paul makes a promise to the church of Philippi.

00:10:01.000 --> 00:10:07.000
It's a striking comment that is worthy of our consideration tonight.

00:10:07.000 --> 00:10:12.000
Paul writes, Now ye Philippians know also, that in the beginning of the gospel,

00:10:12.000 --> 00:10:17.000
when I departed from Macedonia, no church communicated with me as concerning

00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:21.000
giving and receiving, but ye only.

00:10:21.000 --> 00:10:24.000
Now please, please don't misunderstand.

00:10:24.000 --> 00:10:30.000
Paul isn't saying here that no other church ever supported him at any time

00:10:30.000 --> 00:10:34.000
during his missions endeavors, because we know from studying his epistles

00:10:34.000 --> 00:10:38.000
in the New Testament of the Bible, they certainly did.

00:10:38.000 --> 00:10:42.000
However, here in verse 15, he is calling our attention to the fact

00:10:42.000 --> 00:10:47.000
that at the earliest stage of his missions ministry,

00:10:47.000 --> 00:10:53.000
when the work that God had called him to do was young and vulnerable,

00:10:53.000 --> 00:10:57.000
during that particular season of his ministry,

00:10:57.000 --> 00:11:01.000
no other church entered into partnership with him

00:11:01.000 --> 00:11:06.000
in a structural, repetitive sense of giving and receiving,

00:11:06.000 --> 00:11:11.000
but this church, the church of Philippi.

00:11:11.000 --> 00:11:15.000
When Paul needed support the most,

00:11:15.000 --> 00:11:19.000
Philippi alone stepped forward to help.

00:11:19.000 --> 00:11:26.000
Others had opportunity, but failed to take advantage of it.

00:11:26.000 --> 00:11:30.000
But not this church, not the church of Philippi.

00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:38.000
The church of Philippi was the church that refused to miss its opportunity in missions.

00:11:38.000 --> 00:11:43.000
According to the text before us, when other churches remained silent,

00:11:43.000 --> 00:11:48.000
this, ladies and gentlemen, was the church that spoke up.

00:11:48.000 --> 00:11:53.000
When other churches hesitated, this is the church that helped.

00:11:53.000 --> 00:11:58.000
When others missed the moment, this, ladies and gentlemen,

00:11:58.000 --> 00:12:03.000
was the local New Testament church that seized the moment.

00:12:03.000 --> 00:12:07.000
And therefore I must say, this local New Testament church

00:12:07.000 --> 00:12:14.000
set a tremendous example for the Fellowship Baptist Church of Oakton, Virginia.

00:12:14.000 --> 00:12:16.000
Hear me this evening, Christian friend.

00:12:16.000 --> 00:12:20.000
Today, as we continue this Missions Emphasis Week,

00:12:21.000 --> 00:12:25.000
you and I have set before us a great, may I say again,

00:12:25.000 --> 00:12:27.000
a great opportunity.

00:12:27.000 --> 00:12:30.000
And the opportunity that I'm speaking of

00:12:30.000 --> 00:12:36.000
is the opportunity to invest in world evangelism.

00:12:36.000 --> 00:12:39.000
It's an opportunity that, according to the Bible,

00:12:39.000 --> 00:12:45.000
pays great dividends, not only here on the earth below,

00:12:45.000 --> 00:12:49.000
but even more importantly, in glory itself.

00:12:49.000 --> 00:12:54.000
However, I believe it's just as vitally important for me to remind you

00:12:54.000 --> 00:12:58.000
that opportunity isn't permanent.

00:12:58.000 --> 00:13:00.000
Can I say that again?

00:13:00.000 --> 00:13:04.000
Opportunity isn't permanent. Oh, no, no.

00:13:04.000 --> 00:13:06.000
Opportunity passes.

00:13:06.000 --> 00:13:09.000
Churches can miss it.

00:13:09.000 --> 00:13:13.000
Believers can miss it.

00:13:13.000 --> 00:13:17.000
God's people, they can miss it.

00:13:17.000 --> 00:13:22.000
And therefore God sent me here tonight to implore each and every one of you,

00:13:22.000 --> 00:13:27.000
please don't miss it.

00:13:27.000 --> 00:13:30.000
Please allow me an opportunity to remind you

00:13:30.000 --> 00:13:35.000
that what we do for Christ, we must do quickly.

00:13:35.000 --> 00:13:38.000
There is no time for delay.

00:13:38.000 --> 00:13:45.000
In fact, delayed obedience is nothing less than disobedience.

00:13:45.000 --> 00:13:49.000
Jesus said in the Gospel of John chapter number 4,

00:13:49.000 --> 00:13:53.000
Say not ye there yet four months, and then cometh harvest?

00:13:53.000 --> 00:13:58.000
Behold, I say unto you, lift up your eyes and look on the fields,

00:13:58.000 --> 00:14:01.000
for they are white.

00:14:01.000 --> 00:14:06.000
Jesus said they are white already to harvest.

00:14:06.000 --> 00:14:10.000
That word white here in John chapter 4

00:14:10.000 --> 00:14:16.000
isn't referring to purity, but rather to ripeness.

00:14:16.000 --> 00:14:21.000
Do you see what Jesus is doing in the Gospel of John chapter 4?

00:14:21.000 --> 00:14:25.000
Jesus, in essence, in the minds of his disciples,

00:14:25.000 --> 00:14:28.000
he is painting a picture.

00:14:28.000 --> 00:14:33.000
The word white here is referring to the fact

00:14:33.000 --> 00:14:38.000
that the crop has reached a very decisive moment.

00:14:38.000 --> 00:14:43.000
And to delay the harvest ultimately means loss.

00:14:43.000 --> 00:14:48.000
Here Christ is deliberately contrasting

00:14:48.000 --> 00:14:53.000
human calculation with divine urgency.

00:14:53.000 --> 00:14:58.000
The disciples were no doubt thinking in terms of agricultural timelines

00:14:58.000 --> 00:15:03.000
while Christ was speaking of spiritual opportunity.

00:15:03.000 --> 00:15:08.000
And do you realize in essence what our Savior is saying to the disciples

00:15:08.000 --> 00:15:10.000
in John's Gospel?

00:15:10.000 --> 00:15:15.000
He is saying to them then what he is leading me to tell you tonight.

00:15:15.000 --> 00:15:19.000
What we do for Jesus, the souls we win for Jesus,

00:15:19.000 --> 00:15:21.000
the churches we plant for Jesus,

00:15:21.000 --> 00:15:24.000
those we make a difference in,

00:15:24.000 --> 00:15:29.000
in the days to come, friend, we best get busy doing it.

00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:32.000
Don't miss your opportunity.

00:15:32.000 --> 00:15:35.000
According to the text we've read together tonight,

00:15:35.000 --> 00:15:38.000
the church of Philippi didn't miss it.

00:15:38.000 --> 00:15:41.000
And I'll be praying for the remaining portion of this week

00:15:41.000 --> 00:15:45.000
that neither will you.

00:15:45.000 --> 00:15:49.000
Please allow me to call your attention if I may to just a few truths

00:15:49.000 --> 00:15:52.000
directly from the text tonight

00:15:52.000 --> 00:15:57.000
concerning the opportunity that wasn't missed in missions.

00:15:57.000 --> 00:16:00.000
First of all, notice when I look into these verses of Scripture

00:16:00.000 --> 00:16:06.000
I see number one, a singular partnership.

00:16:06.000 --> 00:16:10.000
I see a singular partnership.

00:16:10.000 --> 00:16:14.000
Notice again if you would please what Paul writes in verse 15.

00:16:14.000 --> 00:16:18.000
Paul writes, now ye Philippians know also that in the beginning of the Gospel

00:16:18.000 --> 00:16:22.000
when I departed from Macedonia, no church,

00:16:22.000 --> 00:16:27.000
watch this next word now, don't miss it, communicated.

00:16:27.000 --> 00:16:31.000
No church communicated with me

00:16:31.000 --> 00:16:34.000
as concerning giving and receiving,

00:16:34.000 --> 00:16:39.000
but ye only, again, notice the word communicated.

00:16:39.000 --> 00:16:42.000
The word communicated in verse 15

00:16:42.000 --> 00:16:46.000
carries the idea of fellowship.

00:16:46.000 --> 00:16:49.000
The word communicated in verse 15

00:16:49.000 --> 00:16:53.000
carries the idea of partnership

00:16:53.000 --> 00:16:57.000
or of joint participation.

00:16:57.000 --> 00:17:02.000
The word communicated assures us tonight, ladies and gentlemen,

00:17:02.000 --> 00:17:06.000
this was not a casual charity

00:17:06.000 --> 00:17:10.000
that the Philippian believers had involved themselves in.

00:17:10.000 --> 00:17:12.000
Absolutely not.

00:17:12.000 --> 00:17:16.000
It was most definitely a covenant cooperation.

00:17:17.000 --> 00:17:22.000
It was not a partnership formed out of convenience,

00:17:22.000 --> 00:17:25.000
but rather out of commitment.

00:17:25.000 --> 00:17:27.000
And let me tell you why.

